   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>To N.N., Aniketos, Ptolemaios and Isidoros, contractors for the tax on sales for the 14th year, from Apollonios son of Hermogenes. I undertake to pay for the initiation of the tax on sales, on condition that, taking the proper receipts as regards the banker and agoranomos, I [rightly?] conduct with them the business of the individuals so that the contract incurs no loss, 500 drachmas a month, which makes 1 talent for the year. � will act with me � [The 14th year, Thoth ?] 15.</ab>
